  [2] I mean, presumably it would be a guarantee against a risk of loss, no=
t just a cash payment, so it's some fraction of $5 billion depending on how=
 likely the losses are, but the point is it's symmetric; eventually the gov=
ernment writes a check and the buyer cashes it.


  [3] If you are an AT1 holder and your reply is "same goes for the common =
stock," I mean, fair, I don't disagree. But each of these decisions is a ro=
