<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Elsewhere in US bank rescues</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Things seem <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloom=
bergbusiness.com/click/30923484.257437/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9u=
ZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDMtMjEvZmlyc3QtcmVwdWJsaWMtcmVzY3VlLW1heS1yZWx5LW9=
uLXVzLWJhY2tpbmctdG8tZmFjaWxpdGF0ZS1kZWFsP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAzMjIyM19NT05FWVNUVU=
ZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDMyM=
iZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB71bca7c8" itempr=
op=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: =
#000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border=
-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;=
">  less urgent at First Republic</a>?</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Wall Street leaders and US officials discussin=
g an intervention at First Republic Bank are exploring the possibility of g=
overnment backing to encourage a deal that would shore up the lender, peopl=
e with knowledge of the situation said. The shares dropped Wednesday mornin=
g.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The group has floated a variety of measures to=
 make the company more attractive to potential investors or a buyer, part o=
f an effort to ensure there isn=E2=80=99t another US bank failure, the peop=
le said, asking not to be named describing confidential talks.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Among options, the government could play a rol=
e in lifting assets out of First Republic that have eroded its balance shee=
t. While investors have expressed interest in helping, the firm=E2=80=99s u=
nrealized losses have been a sticking point. Additional ideas have included=
 offering liability protection, applying capital rules more flexibly or eas=
ing limits on ownership stakes, the people said.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The talks are continuing. A variety of issues =
remain unresolved and an agreement isn=E2=80=99t guaranteed, the people sai=
d. It=E2=80=99s unclear how the government would provide any financial supp=
ort.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Imagine putting dollar numbers on the investor=
s=E2=80=99 demands. Imagine some bigger bank saying =E2=80=9Cokay we=E2=80=
=99ll buy First Republic but we want $5 billion of goodies from the governm=
ent in exchange.=E2=80=9D Goodies might include:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The government buying or guaranteeing=
 some of the worse assets.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The gov=
ernment indemnifying the buyer against some liabilities.</li>=09<li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">=E2=80=9CApplying capital rules more flexibly.=E2=
=80=9D</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">=E2=80=9CEasing limits on o=
wnership stakes.=E2=80=9D</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And the bank has some schedule of how it value=
s each goodie and is indifferent to any package that totals $5 billion wort=
h of goodies. It is I guess fairly straightforward to reduce Options 1 and =
2 to dollars, and also pretty symmetric: A $5 billion loss-sharing deal is =
worth about $5 billion to the buyer and costs the government about $5 billi=
on.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #000000=
; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom=
-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: tr=
ansparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a> I bet that a bank could put a price on=C2=A0Option 3; that is, it coul=
d probably calculate how much more profitable it would be with lower capita=
l requirements. Could the government put a price on it? Is that price symme=
tric? Does saying =E2=80=9Csure, big bank, be undercapitalized for a while=
=E2=80=9D cost the government as much as it benefits the buyer bank? More? =
Less? Has the value of financial stability (and thus bank capital) gone up =
due to this crisis, or is taking a bit of risk with capital requirements a =
cheap way out of it?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Meanwhile <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombe=
rgbusiness.com/click/30923484.257437/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZX=
dzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDMtMjEvYWZ0ZXItc2lnbmF0dXJlLWRlYWwtZmRpYy1pcy1sZWZ0L=
XdpdGgtMTEtYmlsbGlvbi1pbi10b3hpYy13YXN0ZS1sb2Fucz9jbXBpZD1CQkQwMzIyMjNfTU9O=
RVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0=
yMzAzMjImdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB0db9dd5f"=
 itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"=
color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px;=
 border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color=
: #ccc;">  at Signature Bank</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Signature Bank=E2=80=99s partial takeover by a=
 competitor is notable for what it doesn=E2=80=99t include: $11 billion of =
loans against a class of New York City apartments whose values have tumbled=
 in recent years.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In a deal with the Federal Deposit Insurance C=
orp., New York Community Bancorp Inc. is buying more than $34 billion in Si=
gnature=E2=80=99s deposits, as well as $13 billion in loans and 40 bank bra=
nches. Left behind is the commercial real estate debt portfolio, weighted h=
eavily toward multifamily buildings bound by a law that restricts landlords=
=E2=80=99 ability to raise rents.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s toxic waste,=E2=80=9D sa=
id Christopher Whalen, chairman of Whalen Global Advisors. =E2=80=9CFrom an=
 investor point of view, these are dead assets.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/30923484.257437/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9u=
L2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDMtMTMvc3ZiLWNvdWxkbi10LWlnbm9yZS1pdHMtbG9zc2VzLWJ1dC1=
0aGUtZmVkLWNhbj9jbXBpZD1CQkQwMzIyMjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJn=
V0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzAzMjImdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c=
3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa52f5d44" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  basic story</a> of thi=
s month=E2=80=99s US bank runs seems to be that interest rates went up and =
the value of regional banks=E2=80=99 portfolios of safe held-to-maturity bo=
nds went down. These values were not reflected in the banks=E2=80=99 financ=
ial statements (because accounting rules allow them to mark held-to-maturit=
y bonds at their purchase price), but they were reflected in the footnotes =
to those statements, and eventually analysts and depositors read those foot=
notes and got nervous and took their money out. And so SVB and Signature fa=
iled and were seized by the FDIC.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But meanwhile those banks also have loans, and=
 the loans (1) might have some credit problems and (2) probably also have s=
ome interest-rate problems, since they were mostly made in much lower-inter=
est-rate environments. But the loans are harder to value and harder to sell=
; there is not some table at the back of the financial statements listing t=
he exact market value of the loan portfolio. The loans probably did not bri=
ng down the banks. But now that the FDIC owns these banks, it can sell the =
bond portfolios easily enough: They=E2=80=99re just bonds. It turns out tha=
t no one wants some of the loans, though, so the FDIC is stuck with them.</=
p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/30923484.257437/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2Fy=
dGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDMtMjIvcGFjd2VzdC1zYXlzLWl0LWdvdC0xLTQtYmlsbGlvbi1mcm9tLWF=
0bGFzLWZpbmFuY2luZy1mYWNpbGl0eT9jbXBpZD1CQkQwMzIyMjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbW=
VkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzAzMjImdXRtX2Nhb=
XBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB5c42397f" itemprop=3D"Story=
Link" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; te=
xt-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-col=
or: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  at PacW=
est</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">PacWest Bancorp is moving to shore up liquidit=
y to protect itself after customers pulled 20% of their deposits since the =
start of the year.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The regional bank, whose shares have tumbled 5=
8% this month, obtained $1.4 billion from a financing facility from Apollo =
Global Management-owned investment firm Atlas SP Partners and abandoned a s=
eparate push to raise capital because of market volatility, it said in a st=
atement Wednesday.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It used to be that banks funded themselves wit=
h deposits and used the money to make loans to private equity firms. Now ba=
nks fund themselves with loans from private equity firms.</p>
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">AT1s</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A general dynamic in bank rescues is:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You want the shareholders of the fail=
ed bank to take big losses, because (1) the whole point of equity capital a=
t a bank is to bear losses before depositors or taxpayers and (2) you want =
to punish the shareholders to=C2=A0discourage=C2=A0<em>other=C2=A0</em>bank=
s from taking dumb risks.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">To avoid=
 contagion, you want all the=C2=A0<em>other</em>=C2=A0banks to shore up the=
ir balance sheets by selling stock to raise loss-absorbing equity capital.<=
/li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There is a tension here. If you seize the risk=
iest bank and give its shareholders nothing, to make an example of them, th=
en the second-riskiest bank is going to have a hard time raising equity, wh=
ich means it is more likely to fail and need rescuing itself. If you bail o=
ut the riskiest bank in a way that preserves a lot of value for shareholder=
s, then (1) the second-riskiest bank is going to be a bit more sanguine abo=
ut its own risks and (2) the equity didn=E2=80=99t do much good, did it?</p=
>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Similarly with additional tier 1 capital secur=
ities. We have <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/309=
23484.257437/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMj=
MtMDMtMjAvdWJzLWdvdC1jcmVkaXQtc3Vpc3NlLWZvci1hbG1vc3Qtbm90aGluZz9jbXBpZD1CQ=
kQwMzIyMjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRl=
ciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzAzMjImdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a31=
9a23cB1101f89a" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_b=
lank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bot=
tom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; b=
ackground-color: #ccc;">  talked</a> over the last few days <a href=3D"http=
s://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30923484.257437/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY=
mxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDMtMjEvanBtb3JnYW4taGFkLXNv=
bWUtZmFrZS1uaWNrZWw_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDMyMjIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWF=
pbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwMzIyJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb2=
5leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb386f6c6" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemsc=
ope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoratio=
n: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000;=
 border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  about</a> how Credi=
t Suisse Group AG=E2=80=99s AT1 bonds were wiped out in its forced merger w=
ith UBS Group AG over the weekend, even as Credit Suisse=E2=80=99s sharehol=
ders got about $3 billion of value in the deal. AT1 holders, at Credit Suis=
se and elsewhere, are outraged that they did worse than shareholders, and n=
on-Swiss banking regulators have rushed to assure the market that=C2=A0<em>=
they=C2=A0</em>would never treat AT1s that way. I have argued that it was f=
ine and good to zero the AT1s even while paying the shareholders a bit, but=
 never mind that.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The main point here is that, whether or not th=
e common stock got anything, whether or not the AT1 triggers were met as a =
strict legal matter, this is a rescue in which Swiss authorities are provid=
ing asset guarantees and liquidity backstops and other aid to UBS: a bailou=
t, of sorts, at taxpayer expense, or taxpayer risk anyway. And Credit Suiss=
e had 16 billion Swiss francs of AT1 securities that were intended precisel=
y to avoid that, to bear losses before taxpayers do, to go to zero if a bai=
lout looks=C2=A0necessary. And so the Swiss authorities zeroed the AT1s. If=
 you=E2=80=99re not going to zero the AT1s while doing a government-backsto=
pped rescue of a giant global bank over a weekend, what is the point of the=
 AT1s? If they don=E2=80=99t bear losses here, why bother issuing them, and=
 why treat them as loss-absorbing capital?<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=
=3D"#footnote-3" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important;=
 border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-styl=
e: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; display: inli=
ne-block;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand it is good for banks to issu=
e AT1s, to bear losses in risky times, and <a href=3D"https://link.mail.blo=
ombergbusiness.com/click/30923484.257437/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbn=
