 style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-w=
idth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgr=
ound-color: #ccc;"> now they kind of can=E2=80=99t</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The wipeout of $17bn of Credit Suisse bonds ha=
s thrown into question further issuance in the market for risky bank debt, =
with some of Asia=E2=80=99s biggest banks considering pausing sales.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Major banks in Japan, Singapore and Hong Kong =
are placing new additional tier 1 (AT1) bond deals on hold until market con=
ditions stabilise, according to people familiar with the plans.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The hiatus follows three days of turmoil trigg=
ered by the decision to write down the value of Credit Suisse=E2=80=99s AT1=
 bond to zero as part of the bank=E2=80=99s takeover by Swiss rival UBS, wh=
ile shareholders received $3.25bn. AT1s are a class of debt designed to tak=
e losses when institutions run into trouble but are generally believed to r=
ank ahead of equity on the balance sheet.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Regulators in the eurozone, UK and Hong Kong h=
ave stressed that they will not follow Swiss authorities in upsetting the u=
sual hierarchy of bank creditors.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Even so, prices in the $260bn AT1 market have =
tumbled this week. Analysts and investors have warned that buyers are likel=
y to demand substantially higher borrowing costs, potentially creating a =
=E2=80=9Czombie market=E2=80=9D where banks are reluctant to issue fresh de=
bt to refinance older bonds. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The fallout from the Credit Suisse deal =E2=80=
=9Cchanges the whole nature of the [AT1] market, and I think the ability to=
 issue going forward is probably close to zero=E2=80=9D, said Greg Peters, =
co-chief investment officer of PGIM Fixed Income. =E2=80=9CBasically, it=E2=
=80=99s a zombie market going forward in my mind.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
